---
const updated = "June 2026";
---

<dialog
  id="privacy-dialog"
  tabindex="-1"
  class="bg-surface backdrop:bg-ink/60 m-auto w-[min(34rem,calc(100vw-2rem))] p-0 text-base outline-none"
  aria-labelledby="privacy-title"
>
  <div class="max-h-[85vh] overflow-y-auto p-8">
    <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
      <h2 id="privacy-title" class="text-3xl">Privacy</h2>
      <button
        type="button"
        data-privacy-close
        aria-label="Close"
        class="text-muted hover:text-ink -mt-1 cursor-pointer text-3xl leading-none"
      >
        &times;
      </button>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-4">
      This is a recipe site. It doesn't ask for your name, your email, or anything else about you.
      Here's the full picture of what happens when you visit.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-xl">Analytics</h3>
    <p class="mt-2">
      We use <a href="https://umami.is/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Umami</a>, a
      privacy-friendly analytics tool. It counts visits and shows us aggregated stats like page
      views, referring sites, country, and browser type. It uses <strong>no cookies</strong>,
      collects <strong>no personal data</strong>, and can't track you across other websites.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-xl">Fonts</h3>
    <p class="mt-2">
      The site loads typefaces from Google Fonts. To deliver them, your browser connects to Google's
      servers, which means your IP address is shared with Google as part of that request.
    </p>

    <h3 class="mt-6 text-xl">That's it</h3>
    <p class="mt-2">
      No cookies, no accounts, no advertising, no data sold or shared with anyone else. If you have
      a question, the recipe is the same whether you ask or not.
    </p>

    <p class="text-muted mt-6 text-sm">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <div class="mt-6 text-right">
      <button
        type="button"
        data-privacy-close
        class="bg-accent inline-block cursor-pointer px-5 py-3 text-sm tracking-[0.12em] text-white uppercase"
      >
        Close
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</dialog>

<script>
  const dialog = document.getElementById("privacy-dialog") as HTMLDialogElement | null;
  if (dialog) {
    document.querySelectorAll("[data-privacy-open]").forEach((el) =>
      el.addEventListener("click", () => {
        dialog.showModal();
        // showModal() autofocuses the first button (the ×); move focus to the
        // dialog itself so nothing shows a focus ring on open.
        dialog.focus();
      }),
    );
    dialog
      .querySelectorAll("[data-privacy-close]")
      .forEach((el) => el.addEventListener("click", () => dialog.close()));
    dialog.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
      if (e.target === dialog) dialog.close();
    });
  }
</script>
